TITLE: Configuring References with @prop in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the 'ref' option with @prop to set up references between models. It shows both single and array reference examples, using both class and string-based references.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typegoose/typegoose/blob/master/docs/api/decorators/prop.md#2025-04-17_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
class Kitten {
  @prop()
  public name?: string;
}

class Cat {
  // single examples
  @prop({ ref: () => Kitten })
  public kitten?: Ref<Kitten>;
  // or
  @prop({ ref: 'Kitten' })
  public kitten?: Ref<Kitten>;

  // array examples
  @prop({ ref: () => Kitten })
  public kittens?: Ref<Kitten>[];
  // or
  @prop({ ref: 'Kitten' })
  public kittens?: Ref<Kitten>[];
}
```

