TITLE: Converting Traditional Mongoose Model to Typegoose in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: A comparison showing how to convert a traditional Mongoose schema and model to a Typegoose class with proper TypeScript type definitions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typegoose/typegoose/blob/master/docs/guides/quick-start-guide.md#2025-04-17_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const kittenSchema = new mongoose.Schema({
  name: String
});

const KittenModel = mongoose.model('Kitten', kittenSchema);

let document = await KittenModel.create({ name: 'Kitty' });
// "document" has basic mongoose inferred types
```

