TITLE: Comparing Native Mongoose and Typegoose Schema Creation
DESCRIPTION: This snippet compares how to create a schema with a sub-document in both native Mongoose and Typegoose, showing the equivalent implementations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typegoose/typegoose/blob/master/docs/guides/faq.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// Native Mongoose
const subSchema = new mongoose.Schema({ someprop: { type: String } });
const mainSchema = new mongoose.Schema({
  subDoc: subSchema
})

// Typegoose
class Sub {
  @prop()
  public someprop: string;
}

class Main {
  @prop()
  public subDoc: Sub; // by reflection, not explicitly defining option "type"
  // OR
  @prop({ type: () => Sub }) // defining option "type" explicitly
  public subDoc: Sub;
}
```

