TITLE: Custom Validation with @prop in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the 'validate' option with @prop to set custom validation rules for properties. It includes an example of a custom validator function with an error message.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typegoose/typegoose/blob/master/docs/api/decorators/prop.md#2025-04-17_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// "maxlength" already exists as an option, this just shows how to use validate
class Validated {
  @prop({
    validate: {
      validator: (v) => {
        return v.length <= 10;
      },
      message: 'value is over 10 characters long!'
    }
  })
  public validated?: string;
}
```

