TITLE: Setting _id Manually in Typegoose
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to properly set the _id field in Typegoose models, with examples showing default behavior and custom ID generation using UUID.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typegoose/typegoose/blob/master/docs/guides/faq.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// not overwriting the defaults
class Main {
  // no "@prop" because of not wanting to overwrite the defaults
  public _id!: mongoose.Types.ObjectId;
}

class Main2 {
  // overwrite the "_id" type to be a string and generated by a uuidv4 function
  @prop({ required: true, default: () => uuidv4() })
  public _id!: string;
}
```

