TITLE: Defining Map Types in Typegoose
DESCRIPTION: Shows various ways to define Map types in Typegoose, including primitive types, arrays, and nested documents.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typegoose/typegoose/blob/master/docs/api/decorators/prop.md#2025-04-17_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
class SomeMapClass1 {
  @prop({ type: String })
  public lookup?: Map<string, string>; // "Map<any, any>" or "mongoose.Types.Map<any>" is needed to be detected as a Map
}

class SomeMapClass2 {
