TITLE: Example Usage of isDocumentArray Type Guard
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the isDocumentArray function to check if an array of references contains only Mongoose documents, allowing for proper type narrowing in TypeScript.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typegoose/typegoose/blob/master/docs/api/functions/typeguards/isDocument.md#2025-04-17_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
class Cat {
  @prop({ ref: 'Cat' })
  public kittens: Ref<Cat>;

  // this example could be smaller, but for demonstation purposes this is a longer version
