TITLE: Example of Ref Option is Undefined Error [E005]
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates code that would trigger the E005 error, which occurs when the ref option is undefined or null in a property decorator.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typegoose/typegoose/blob/master/docs/guides/error-warning-details.md#2025-04-17_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
class ErrorClass {
  @prop({ ref: () => undefined }) // <- error here
  public someProp?: Ref<ErrorClass>;

  @prop({ ref: undefined }) // <- error here
  public someProp?: Ref<ErrorClass>;
}
```

